inspiration to heathen cultures."]28 [Sharp-witted and funny but never
mean, she's a memorialist a bit like Truman Capote,]29 [if he'd been
Jewish and female and less bitchy.]30

[Little Lily,]31 [as Ms. Cunningham calls herself in the book,]32
[really wasn't ordinary.]33 [She was raised, for the first eight
years, by her mother, Rosie,]34 [whom she remembers as a loving
